The bulk lifetime is an important parameter for finding the best cell type with POLO junctions for industrial production. In general, the bulk lifetime depends on the cell process due to gettering effects and defect kinetics. This is especially true for p-type Si wafers. We, therefore, vary the bulk lifetime of the various cell types to analyze the sensitivity of the efficiency to bulk lifetime variations. The cell geometries are those optimized for high lifetimes. The optimized front finger pitch, however, depends mainly on the trade-off between resistance contributions and shading. Therefore, the variation of the optimum finger pitch with varying lifetime is small. Figure 7 shows the efficiencies of all cell types as a function of a fixed, i.e. injection-independent, SRH bulk lifetime. The lifetime has only a minor effect on the efficiencies of the PERC+ and PERC+ POLO concepts of less than 0.5% for lifetimes between 500 μs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
