				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text{POLO}^2$$\end{document} concepts as bottom cells for 2- and 3-terminal devices. The analysis of these tandem cells is not part of this study but we estimate an efficiency of above 33% by adding an approximate 21% efficiency for the top and half of the efficiency simulated here for the bottom cell. The roadmap shown in Fig. 8 is one possibility for approaching highest efficiencies. It is, however, also possible to directly develop POLO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
